If the counsel and other help provided under subsection (b) of this section do not result in feasible or successful proposals, or if other action is necessary to assure the public health of the underserved area, the Secretary may:
Provide the needed health care facilities, staff, or services by contract with one or more physicians, hospitals, or other medical groups or personnel; or
To facilitate the provision of State health care services to the underserved area, approve a contract or other written arrangement with a public or private health care entity, including:
A federally qualified health center;
A health care facility, as defined in § 19-114 of this article;
A health benefit plan or insurance carrier;
A health maintenance organization;
A managed care organization; and
Any other entity that finances the provision of or delivers health care services to the area.
